[1]
Date: 6 May 2010
Source: The Dispatch [edited]
<http://www.the-dispatch.com/article/20100506/ARTICLES/100509938?Title=Davidson-County-reports-second-case-of-rabies>


The Davidson County Health Department reports the 2nd case of rabies
for the year 2010.

A cat caught and killed a rabid bat Tuesday [4 May 2010] in the Hasty
community. The cat was not properly vaccinated and has been
destroyed. There was no human exposure reported.

Do not handle your animal with bare hands after it has had contact
with a wild animal. Saliva from the wild animal may still be present
on the domestic animal's fur, and by handling the animal, you may
expose yourself to the rabies virus.

If there are stray dogs, cats or wildlife in your neighborhood, call
Animal Control at 249-0131. Call the Rabies Hotline at 242-2348 if
you or your pet comes in contact with another animal.

--
