[Rabies state law varies slightly from state to state regarding
length of quarantine when an animal has been previously vaccinated.

However, almost all states are clear that unvaccinated animals with
known rabies exposure are to be euthanized. The risk of transmitting
this fatal disease to humans is high in such circumstances.

All pets should be vaccinated against rabies. This includes those
large animal pets such as horses and show cattle or animals with
valuable genetics.

All of these articles urge people not to touch a dead animal that may
have rabies. People should wash their hands with soap and warm water
after any possible contact with a rabid animal. If you are bitten or
scratched by a wild animal or any animal you do not know, then seek
appropriate medial attention as you may need post exposure
prophylaxis to prevent rabies in yourself. - Mod.TG]
